# Views

Views call controller methods and render atoms — no logic, no state management.

## Standard pattern
```dart
class RewardsView extends StatelessWidget {
  static final _controller = RewardsController();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    _controller.loadRewards();

    return Scaffold(
      body: rewards(
        success: RewardsList.new,
        failure: ErrorText.new,
        loading: RewardsShimmer.new,
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Calling controller methods
```dart
// fire and forget — view reacts via atom
ElevatedButton(
  onPressed: _controller.refresh,
  child: const Text('Refresh'),
)

// when the view needs to react to the result directly (snackbar, navigation)
final result = await _controller.createPreOrder(id: id);
if (result is Success) {
  ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(...);
}
```

## Local UI state
```dart
final isSelected = Atom(false);

// render conditionally
isSelected((_) => const SelectedIndicator())

// with fallback
isSelected(
  (_) => const SelectedIndicator(),
  fallback: const UnselectedIndicator(),
)

// when you need the value
searchQuery((value) => Text(value))
```

## Widget convention
Widgets used as constructor references must accept the value as a single positional argument:
```dart
// correct
class RewardsList extends StatelessWidget {
  const RewardsList(this.rewards, {super.key});
  final List<RewardModel> rewards;
}

// wrong — named param, cannot be passed as constructor reference
class RewardsList extends StatelessWidget {
  const RewardsList({super.key, required this.rewards});
}
```

## Rules
- `StatefulWidget` only for animation controllers or focus nodes — not for state management
- Controller as static field: `static final _controller = FeatureController()`
- Call `loadData()` in `build()` — safe because controllers return early if cached
- Never use `setState` for app state
- Never put business logic in views
- Never use `BuildContext` in controllers or services
- Extract sub-widgets early to avoid deep nesting
- `const` constructors wherever possible
